value.title: Trump 'coyote' remark confuses Twitter, including Georgia state Democrat
value.excerpt: When President Trump suggested at the Thursday presidential debate that the more than 500 migrant children who the government hasn’t been able to reunite with their parents were brought to the border by coyotes, many on social media were left confused.

value.title: Pence calls on Biden to 'come forward and come clean' with answers on son Hunter's scandal
value.excerpt: Vice President Mike Pence called on his predecessor, Joe Biden, to be frank and honest with the American people Friday about whether he was involved in or benefited from his son Hunter's overseas business interests.

value.title: Democratic Rep. Xochitl Torres Small slams Biden over oil remarks at debate, says policy is 'out of touch'
value.excerpt: Biden said he would pursue policies that would “transition from the oil industry” if elected to office.

value.title: Biden's early White House transition plans negotiate pressure from both ends of political spectrum
value.excerpt: Democratic presidential nominee Joe Biden has not yet been elected to the office, but he's planning his transition as though he has been.

value.title: Gregg Jarrett: Hunter Biden laptop scandal — Even if Joe Biden wins, there's no way out now
value.excerpt: In the Hunter Biden laptop scandal, the unresolved and trenchant questions are: how much did Joe Biden know and to what extent was he involved

value.title: Joy Behar says Trump should be charged with ‘crimes against humanity’ over immigration policy
value.excerpt: The View” co-host Joy Behar said on Friday that President Trump and members of his administration should be charged with “crimes against humanity” because of its immigration policy and vowed to not “be a part of a country” that separates children from their parents.

value.title: Trump announces peace deal between Sudan and Israel, says more nations will normalize relations
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump announced Friday that Sudan will start to normalize ties with Israel, making it the third Arab state to do so as part of U.S.-brokered deals in the run-up to Election Day.

value.title: FBI asks to interview Hunter Biden ex-associate Bobulinski, Senate committee says
value.excerpt: The FBI has asked former Hunter Biden business associate Tony Bobulinski to sit for an interview Friday, Bobulinski's lawyers told the Senate Homeland Security Committee, which released a statement Friday.

value.title: Biden will ‘campaign aggressively’ in final stretch, top aide insists
value.excerpt: When it comes to the number of in-person campaign events being held in the White House race, President Trump is lapping Democratic nominee Joe Biden.

value.title: Man arrested in North Carolina with van full of guns, explosives, planned to assassinate Joe Biden: Report
value.excerpt: A man arrested in North Carolina and being held in jail on child pornography charges allegedly also was plotting to carry out an act of terrorism, including an assassination attempt on Democratic presidential nominee Joe Biden.

value.title: McConnell on Biden’s court commission plan: ‘Court packing ought to be completely unacceptable’
value.excerpt: Sen. Majority Leader Mitch McConnell said that Joe Biden’s plan to form a commission to “reform” the court system meant that he was “open to” court packing.

value.title: Trump lambasts Lesley Stahl for pressing him on 'tough questions': 'That's no way to talk'
value.excerpt: President Trump, in a testy interview with CBS's Lesly Stahl, chastized the veteran reporter telling her "that's no way to talk" when she ribbed him about his ability to take "tough questions" during an interview meant to air on 60 Minutes on Sunday.

value.title: Trump claims Obama 'campaigning for us' after former president's scathing rebuke
value.excerpt: President Trump claimed that former President Obama was campaigning for him “every time he speaks,” after Trump’s predecessor slammed him at a rally for Joe Biden Wednesday night.

value.title: Trump’s Mission: Burn it down
value.excerpt: Trump can’t beat Biden as Biden is currently defined.

value.title: 'No surprise' Russia and Iran want Trump out: National Security Adviser O'Brien
value.excerpt: National Security Adviser Robert O'Brien explained on “Fox & Friends” on Thursday why he believes Iran and Russia allegedly tried to interfere with the 2020 elections.

value.title: Anti-Trump Lincoln Project shared content US later ID'd as Iranian disinformation
value.excerpt: The anti-Trump Lincoln Project PAC shared content on Twitter that U.S. intelligence officials later labeled as Iranian disinformation.

value.title: Donna Brazile confident Joe Biden will handle Hunter email controversy: 'Bring it up!'
value.excerpt: Joe Biden should not let President Trump interrupt him during the final presidential debate Thursday night, former DNC Interim Chair Donna Brazile argues.

value.title: If Biden wins and Dems control Congress, SCOTUS will be expanded: Graham
value.excerpt: Joe Biden and the Democratic Party want to expand the Supreme Court to at least 13 seats to make it liberal if Republicans succeed in confirming Amy Coney Barrett, Sen. Lindsey Graham, R-S.C., told "Fox & Friends" on Thursday.

value.title: NYC joining Portland, Seattle to sue Trump admin over defunding for 'anarchist jurisdictions'
value.excerpt: New York City is joining Seattle and Portland, Ore., to file a complaint against the Trump administration in a Seattle court.

value.title: Harris, prominent Democrats listed as 'key contacts' for Biden family business venture projects
value.excerpt: EXCLUSIVE: A list of “key domestic contacts” for a joint venture involving Jim and Hunter Biden and now-bankrupt CEFC China Energy Co. included former Vice President Joe Biden's current running mate Sen. Kamala Harris, among other prominent Democrats, Fox News has learned.

value.title: Linda Ronstadt slams Donald Trump's 'state of emergency' at the U.S. southern border, 'encouraging resentment'
value.excerpt: Linda Ronstadt bashed Donald Trump and his administration’s handling of the situation at the United States’ southern border.

value.title: Biden faces backlash for saying 'America was an idea' that 'we've never lived up to'
value.excerpt: Joe Biden was facing intense backlash Wednesday night for referring to America as an "idea" that "we've never lived up to."

value.title: Ingraham: Democrats hiding 'true agenda' from middle, working class by trotting out Biden cliches
value.excerpt: President Trump, not Joe Biden, is the candidate who truly fights for the working class, Laura Ingraham argued Wednesday on "The Ingraham Angle."

value.title: Hunter Biden: Here's what he has said about his Burisma role in Ukraine
value.excerpt: The son of former Vice President Joe Biden has mostly remained mum on the allegations of impropriety while working on the board of Ukrainian oil company Burisma. Here’s what he has said about it in the past.

value.title: Trump campaign takes over YouTube masthead for debate day with help of UFC supporters
value.excerpt: EXCLUSIVE: President Trump's campaign Thursday will take over YouTube's masthead for 24 hours, controlling the prime internet real estate on the day of final debate between Trump and Democratic nominee Joe Biden, Fox News has learned.

value.title: Jennifer Lawrence says Trump altered her political views: ‘There’s been a line drawn in the sand’
value.excerpt: Jennifer Lawrence said despite the fact she grew up in a Republican household, because of Trump, she has become more open-minded about politics "based on the things I learned."

value.title: Trump envoy Richard Grenell met with Venezuelan politician in bid to oust Maduro: report
value.excerpt: Richard Grenell, the Trump administration's special envoy for Serbia and Kosovo Peace Negotiations, reportedly tried in September to negotiate with a Venezuelan politician close to the country's strongman president, Nicolas Maduro, in order to obtain the controversial leader's peaceful exit from office.

value.title: Trump grants clemency to Alice Marie Johnson associate, 4 other nonviolent criminals
value.excerpt: President Trump granted clemency on Wednesday to five prisoners-- including one who was an associate of Alice Marie Johnson-- who were each serving time in prison for non-violent offenses.

value.title: Blackburn: Trump should focus on his 'incredible record' at presidential debate, not 'Biden Inc.'
value.excerpt: President Trump should focus on his own accomplishments during Thursday night's second and final presidential debate against Joe Biden, Sen. Marsha Blackburn, R-Tenn., told "Special Report" Wednesday.

value.title: Trump campaign, Nevada GOP threaten to sue Clark County over attempts to ‘obstruct’ election observation
value.excerpt: The campaign and state Republicans claim that observers have been banned from certain areas where ballots are handled.
